
This is a Sales Dashboard for 2025 that combines several different views to give a "big picture" look at how a business is performing.

Think of this as a health report for a company. Here is the simple breakdown:

1. The "Big Three" Numbers (Top Row)
At a glance, you can see how much the business has grown compared to the Previous Year (PY):

Total Sales ($733K): This is the total money taken in. It is up by 20.4%.

Total Profit ($93K): This is the money kept after costs. It is up by 14.2%.

Total Quantity ($12K): This is the number of individual items sold. It is up by 26.8%.

The Takeaway: The business is growing significantly in every major category.

2. Performance Over Time (The Sparklines)
Next to each big number is a small line graph showing the trend from January to December.

Black Line: Current Year (2025).

Grey Line: Previous Year.

The Blue dots show the highest points of the year, while the Orange dots show the lowest points.

3. What’s Selling? (Bottom Left)
This section lists product categories like Phones, Chairs, and Tables.

The Left Bars: Compare sales volume. You can see Phones and Chairs are the top sellers.

The Right Bars (Blue & Orange): Show profit.

Blue means they made money (like Copiers).

Orange means they actually lost money selling that item (like Tables and Machines).

4. Weekly Ups and Downs (Bottom Right)
This chart tracks performance week-by-week.

Blue sections: Weeks where sales or profit were above average.

Orange sections: Weeks where they were below average.

You can see a lot of "Blue" toward the end of the year, meaning the business finished 2025 very strongly.
